Message.message: At the apex of the tower.
They call it a god.
A darkness that eats the sun.
The hunt begins
I climb step by ruinous step.
The runes fester, clouding vision.
The walls seeth.
The walls churn.
The walls narrow.
The boxes glide across the floor like evil birds.
Every step grows harder, Every breath heavier.
How high am I?
Every room, the same sickly walls, the same pallid stench of ruin.
The lurid dance of deja vu.
How does this distorted tower even stand?
Circles upon Spirals upon Doom. Doom. Doom!
Will this endless tower ever end?
Am I just lost within a labyrinth?
Hi Protagonist! I'm sorry, but the eldritch horror is in another castle.
All thats left here is a dead sun and sentence fragments.
Also your entire extended family has been kidnapped. Yup. All 37 of them.
But don't worry, we can save them. Hop on my back!
We're going
To
"The Castle On the Moon"
sequel to god slayer, coming soon.
Click the follow button in the top right corner to get notified about the sequel and other puzzles games as soon as they come out.
This plot will definitely have a satisfying, not click bait conclusion.
